(3056, 'Martinked', 'mtskhetag@gmail.com', '81548756112', '-', '-', 'Mobile Balancing System Balanset-1A', 'Dear Colleagues! \r\nWe are pleased to offer modern equipment for imbalance elimination of rotating mechanisms - portable balancing device Balanset-1A. \r\nOfficial product page: https://vibromera.eu/shop/889/ \r\n<a href=\"https://vibromera.eu/shop/889/\"><img src=\"https://vibromera.eu/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/12.webp\" alt=\"Full balancing system\" style=\"max-width: 100%; height: auto; margin: 20px 0;\"></a> \r\n \r\nWhere It\'s Applied \r\nBalanset-1A is actively applied for vibration adjustment of various types rotating mechanisms: \r\nProduction Mechanisms: \r\nVentilation Systems - industrial, centrifugal, axial. Pump Units - centrifugal, chemical. Electric Motors - DC motors. Turbo Units - steam. Compression Equipment - piston. \r\nProcessing Equipment: \r\nTool Spindles - lathe. Grinding Wheels. Roll Equipment of rolling mills. \r\nAgricultural Machinery: \r\nChoppers. Rotary Mowers. Crushers for fertilizers. \r\nSpecialized Machinery: \r\nCentrifugal Equipment - laboratory. Air Blowers. Milling Units. Drive Shafts. \r\n<a href=\"https://vibromera.eu/shop/889/\"><img src=\"https://vibromera.eu/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/1714073479045.jpg\" alt=\"Field balancing on combine harvester\" style=\"max-width: 100%; height: auto; margin: 20px 0;\"></a> \r\n \r\nTechnical Parameters \r\nKey Characteristics: \r\nBalancing planes: One or two. Rotation frequency range: 200 to 15,000 revolutions per minute. Phase error: ┬▒1┬░. Vibration measurement accuracy: ┬▒5%. Measurement channels: 2. Measured vibration velocity: 0.1 to 300 mm/s. Power supply: From computer USB port. Equipment mass: 4 kg. \r\nFunctional Capabilities: \r\nAutomatic calculation of balancing weights. Database of operations. Tolerance calculation according to ISO 1940. FFT analysis of vibration. Data visualization in real time. Split-weight calculator. Index balancing of mandrels. \r\n \r\nDelivery Set \r\nStandard Configuration: \r\n \r\nUSB coupling module (1 pc.) - provides data transfer between sensors and computer. \r\nAccelerometers (2 pcs.) - Conversion factor: 100 mV/g. Operating frequencies: 0.5-10,000 Hz. Mounting: threaded stud. \r\n \r\n<a href=\"https://vibromera.eu/shop/889/\"><img src=\"https://vibromera.eu/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/4-4.webp\" alt=\"Accelerometer with magnetic base\" style=\"max-width: 50%; height: auto; margin: 10px 0;\"></a> \r\n \r\nOptical tachometer (1 pc.) - Operating distance: up to 1.5 m. Non-contact measurement for maximum safety. \r\n \r\n<a href=\"https://vibromera.eu/shop/889/\"><img src=\"https://vibromera.eu/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/ZKqzGXSCCBU.jpg\" alt=\"Digital RPM sensor\" style=\"max-width: 50%; height: auto; margin: 10px 0;\"></a> \r\n \r\nMagnetic stand for phase sensor (1 pc.) - Pull force: 60 kgf. Variable angles for accurate readings. \r\n \r\n<a href=\"https://vibromera.eu/shop/889/\"><img src=\"https://vibromera.eu/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/magnetiline-alus-insize-60-kgf-e0f05_reference-1.jpg\" alt=\"Adjustable sensor mount\" style=\"max-width: 50%; height: auto; margin: 10px 0;\"></a> \r\n \r\nElectronic scales up to 500 g (1 pc.) - Accuracy: 0.01 g. Essential for precise weight measurement. \r\nBalancing software Balanset-1A - Intuitive operation. PC-based. Multilingual interface. \r\n \r\n<a href=\"https://vibromera.eu/shop/889/\"><img src=\"https://vibromera.eu/wp-content/uploads/wpforo/default_attachments/1747606106-Screenshot-2025-05-16-165601.png\" alt=\"Balancing program settings\" style=\"max-width: 80%; height: auto; margin: 10px 0;\"></a> \r\n \r\nProtective case (1 pc.) - Heavy-duty build. Protective padding for secure storage. \r\nTechnical documentation - Detailed instructions. Step-by-step procedures. \r\nConnection cables - High-quality shielded cables. \r\n \r\n \r\nStrong Points of Balanset-1A \r\nTechnical Advantages: \r\n? Accurate Results - Innovative technologies of signal processing provide consistent accuracy. \r\n? Compactness - Easy transportation allows field operations without disassembly. \r\n? Multi-functionality - Suitable for any types rotors from miniature spindles to large turbines. \r\n? User Convenience - User-friendly software bypasses special training. \r\n<a href=\"https://vibromera.eu/shop/889/\"><img src=\"https://vibromera.eu/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/1714073479031.jpg\" alt=\"Professional vibration diagnostics\" style=\"max-width: 100%; height: auto; margin: 20px 0;\"></a> \r\nEconomic Advantages: \r\n? Cost Reduction on operation through timely diagnostics - up to 70% of unexpected breakdowns. \r\n? Equipment Life Extension by 50-200% - properly maintained rotors lasts longer. \r\n? Energy Efficiency by 5-15% - reduced friction save electricity. \r\n? Short ROI Period - from 3 to 12 months depending on usage intensity. \r\n \r\nService \r\nAvailable to you: \r\nPersonnel Training - theoretical sessions online. Advanced training encompasses all aspects. \r\nConsultations - on-site guidance. Phone consultations for quick problem solving. \r\nVerification and Calibration - periodic verification to guarantee reliability. \r\nEquipment Rental - suitable for short-term needs. Monthly rental options available. \r\n<a href=\"https://vibromera.eu/shop/889/\"><img src=\"https://vibromera.eu/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/1714073479102.jpg\" alt=\"Large machinery diagnostics\" style=\"max-width: 100%; height: auto; margin: 20px 0;\"></a> \r\n \r\nPricing \r\nCurrent Pricing: \r\nBalanset-1A Portable Balancer & Vibration Analyzer: Рѓг1,751.00 \r\nBalanset-1A OEM Version: Рѓг1,561.00 \r\nAdditional Vibration Sensor: Рѓг90.00 \r\nOptical Sensor (Laser Tachometer): Рѓг124.00 \r\nMagnetic Stand 60 kgf: Рѓг46.00 \r\nReflective Tape: Рѓг10.00 \r\n<a href=\"https://vibromera.eu/shop/889/\"><img src=\"https://vibromera.eu/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/balkom4-1.jpg\" alt=\"Multi-channel vibration analyzer\" style=\"max-width: 80%; height: auto; margin: 20px 0;\"></a> \r\nDelivery Terms: \r\nDelivery time: from 3 days. Warranty terms: 24 months comprehensive coverage. Payment: negotiable. Shipping: international shipping via courier service. \r\n \r\nWhy We Stand Out \r\n \r\nOfficial Supplier - genuine products with complete service. \r\nCertified Specialists with extensive experience in predictive maintenance. \r\nComprehensive Support - from delivery to support and training. \r\nWarehouse Inventory - minimal lead time for popular models. \r\nFlexible Terms for large orders including preferred rates. \r\n \r\n \r\n<a href=\"https://vibromera.eu/shop/889/\"><img src=\"https://vibromera.eu/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/balkom4.jpg\" alt=\"Full vibration analysis set\" style=\"max-width: 100%; height: auto; margin: 20px 0;\"></a> \r\nAt your service, \r\nBalancing specialists team \r\n \r\nP.S. Request a demonstration of the equipment at your convenience and learn about promotions!', '2025-07-11 16:00:25', '2025-07-11 16:00:25'),
(3057, 'Creatbotd600En', 'almeta_muller@creatbotd6002.com', '89342884229', '-', '-', 'CreatBot D600 Pro Industrial 3D Printer with Dual Extruder', '<p><strong>CreatBot D600 Pro 2 Industrial 3D Printer</strong> is a cutting-edge <strong>3D printing device</strong> designed for professionals demanding accuracy, reliability, and versatility in <strong>3D printing</strong>. As part of the <strong>D600 series</strong>, it incorporates a large build volume, advanced <strong>dual extrusion</strong> technology, and top-tier features suitable for industrial-scale applications and complex materials.</p> \r\n \r\n<h2>Overview of the CreatBot D600 Series</h2> \r\n<p>The <strong>CreatBot D600 Series</strong> and <strong>D600 Pro models</strong> establish new standards for <strong>large format 3D printer</strong> solutions. With a <strong>build volume</strong> of 600 ? 600 ? 600 mm, these <strong>professional large format 3D printers</strong> cater to a broad spectrum of industrial 3D printing demands, from <strong>large model</strong> prototyping to end-use production. The <strong>D600 Pro lineup</strong> and the latest <strong>D600 Pro2 HS</strong> introduce further improvements in performance and material compatibility.</p> \r\n \r\n<h2>Key Features and Advantages</h2> \r\n<h3>Industrial-Grade Large Build Volume</h3> \r\n<ul> \r\n<li><strong>Build volume</strong>: 600 ? 600 ? 600 mm</li> \r\n<li>Ideal for <strong>large format 3D printing</strong> projects and industrial 3D printing</li> \r\n<li>Supports <strong>engineering-grade materials</strong> and complex prototypes</li> \r\n</ul> \r\n \r\n<h3>Dual Extrusion and High-Heat Printing</h3> \r\n<ul> \r\n<li>4th generation <strong>1.75mm dual extruders and hotends</strong> for multi-material printing</li> \r\n<li>Right and <strong>left-side extruder</strong> design for flexible <strong>printing</strong></li> \r\n<li>Supports high performance 3D materials, including <strong>PLA</strong>, <strong>nylon filament</strong>, <strong>carbon fiber</strong>, and more</li> \r\n<li>Maximum <strong>nozzle</strong> temperature: up to 420┬░C (<strong>high-heat</strong>)</li> \r\n<li>Heated build chamber for <strong>premium</strong> applications</li> \r\n</ul> \r\n \r\n<h3>Precision, Speed and Reliability</h3> \r\n<ul> \r\n<li>Professional <strong>3d print</strong> quality with accurate layer resolution</li> \r\n<li>Advanced motion system for <strong>fast printing</strong> and robust performance</li> \r\n<li>Consistent <strong>printing speed</strong> up to 120 mm/s</li> \r\n<li>Reliable operation for continuous industrial use</li> \r\n</ul> \r\n \r\n<h2>Compatible Materials and Filaments</h2> \r\n<h3>Wide Filament Compatibility</h3> \r\n<ul> \r\n<li>Works with a broad spectrum of <strong>filament</strong>: PLA, ABS, PC, PETG, PVA, <strong>nylon</strong>, <strong>carbon-fiber</strong>, and more</li> \r\n<li>Designed for <strong>engineering-grade materials</strong> and functional prototyping</li> \r\n<li>Advanced <strong>dual extruder 3d printer</strong> enables multi-material and soluble support printing</li> \r\n</ul> \r\n \r\n<h2>Applications: From Prototyping to Production</h2> \r\n<p>The <strong>CreatBot D600 Pro 2</strong> and <strong>D600 Pro 3D printer</strong> serve a diverse set of applications:</p> \r\n<ul> \r\n<li>Rapid prototyping and <strong>large scale 3D printing</strong> models</li> \r\n<li>Functional parts for automotive, aerospace, and engineering</li> \r\n<li>Tooling, jigs, and fixtures for industrial production</li> \r\n<li>Art, architecture, and creative projects requiring <strong>large industrial 3D</strong> printing</li> \r\n</ul> \r\n \r\n<h2>Technical Specifications</h2> \r\n<ul> \r\n<li><strong>Model</strong>: CreatBot D600 Pro 2, D600 Pro, D600</li> \r\n<li><strong>Build volume</strong>: 600 ? 600 ? 600 mm</li> \r\n<li><strong>Extruder</strong>: Dual extruder, 4th generation 1.75mm dual extruders and hotends</li> \r\n<li><strong>Maximum extruder temperature</strong>: 420┬░C</li> \r\n<li><strong>Bed temperature</strong>: up to 100┬░C</li> \r\n<li><strong>Filament size</strong>: 1.75 mm</li> \r\n<li><strong>Layer resolution</strong>: 0.05 РђЊ 0.3 mm</li> \r\n<li><strong>Supported filament</strong>: PLA, ABS, PC, PETG, PVA, nylon, carbon fiber, engineering-grade materials</li> \r\n<li><strong>Print speed</strong>: up to 120 mm/s</li> \r\n<li><strong>Enclosure</strong>: Heated, for improved material properties</li> \r\n<li><strong>Control</strong>: Touchscreen interface</li> \r\n<li><strong>File formats</strong>: STL, OBJ, AMF</li> \r\n</ul> \r\n \r\n<h2>Comparing D600 Models</h2> \r\n<h3>Feature Differences</h3> \r\n<ul> \r\n<li><strong>D600</strong>: Entry-level industrial large scale 3d printer for basic applications</li> \r\n<li><strong>D600 Pro model</strong>: Enhanced with heated chamber, auto bed leveling, and wider material support</li> \r\n<li><strong>D600 Pro 2</strong> (<strong>pro version</strong>): Adds higher <strong>printing speed</strong>, improved reliability, and HS (high speed) configuration</li> \r\n</ul> \r\n \r\n<h3>Additional CreatBot Printers</h3> \r\n<ul> \r\n<li><strong>CreatBot D1000 HS</strong> for even larger build volumes</li> \r\n<li><strong>CreatBot lineup</strong> includes industrial and professional 3d printer solutions</li> \r\n</ul> \r\n \r\n<h2>Frequently Asked Questions (FAQ)</h2> \r\n<h3>Compatible Materials for CreatBot D600 Pro 2</h3> \r\n<p>The <strong>D600 Pro 2</strong> is compatible with a wide range of <strong>filament types</strong> including PLA, ABS, PETG, PC, <strong>nylon filament</strong>, <strong>carbon-fiber</strong>, and other engineering-grade materials.</p> \r\n \r\n<h3>Maximum Build Volume of D600 Pro 2</h3> \r\n<p>The <strong>printing volume</strong> is 600 ? 600 ? 600 mm, supporting <strong>large model</strong> and industrial 3d printing needs.</p> \r\n \r\n<h3>Dual Extruder and High-Temp Support on D600 Pro 2</h3> \r\n<p>Yes, it is equipped with <strong>dual extrusion</strong> technology and reaches up to 420┬░C for high-temperature <strong>printing</strong>.</p> \r\n \r\n<h3>Differences Between D600 Pro 2 and D600 Pro</h3> \r\n<p>The <strong>D600 Pro 2</strong> offers higher <strong>print speed</strong>, improved reliability, and the new HS (high speed) option.</p> \r\n \r\n<h2>Conclusion</h2> \r\n<p>The <strong>D600 Pro 2</strong> and the <strong>D600 Pro</strong> set the benchmark in the <strong>industrial large scale 3d printer</strong> category. With exceptional <strong>build volume</strong>, robust <strong>dual extrusion system</strong>, compatibility with <strong>engineering-grade materials</strong>, and <strong>top performance</strong> across applications, they empower businesses and engineers to achieve new heights in <strong>industrial 3d printing</strong>.</p> \r\n \r\n<a href=https://creatbotd6002.com>d1000</a>\r\n<a href=https://www.creatbotd6002.com/dual+extruder>dual extruder</a>\r\n<a href=http://creatbotd6002.com/industrial+3d>industrial 3d</a>\r\n<a href=http://creatbotd6002.com/high+performance+3d>high performance 3d</a>', '2025-07-11 16:10:59', '2025-07-11 16:10:59'),
