(3738, 'Mike', 'stark.mike@tryibeta.com', '619-822-1960', 'mobile-app-development', 'iBeta', 'QA Overflow', 'Hi AppsNation team,\r\n\r\nI was looking at your mobile, web and XR builds and figured I would drop a note.\r\n\r\nWe have been helping dev shops like yours handle the part that usually slows everything down, QA. When you are shipping Android, iOS, cross-platform and wearable apps for advertising, healthcare, retail and gaming clients, the test matrix explodes. Devices, OS versions, screen sizes, accessibility rules, API edge cases and performance baselines all have to be checked before the client sees the build, and that work either eats nights and weekends or becomes the reason a release slips.\r\n\r\nAgencies bring us in as their on-demand lab and extra QA crew. We spin up the full device grid, run the automated regression overnight and return tickets that your developers can pick up and close right away, so you can tell every client the app has been independently validated on the hardware and browsers their users actually have.\r\n\r\nOpen to a short call on how we could give AppsNation back those evenings and keep your launches on schedule?\r\n\r\nIf that sounds useful let me know a few times that work or grab a slot here https://calendly.com/ibeta-qa/intro\r\n\r\nAll the best,\r\nMike Stark', '2026-02-10 13:10:59', '2026-02-10 13:10:59'),
